---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = 'Automation Workflow | sddc.info';
const description = 'End-to-end automation workflow from bare-metal provisioning to production-ready Kubernetes cluster deployment.';
const canonicalURL = '/workflow';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonicalURL={canonicalURL}>
  <div class="glass-card p-8 mb-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gradient mb-4">Automation Workflow</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">The complete automation journey from bare-metal servers to production-ready Kubernetes infrastructure.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="glass-card p-8 mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Workflow Overview</h2>
    <p class="mb-6 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Our automation workflow transforms bare-metal servers into a fully functional Kubernetes cluster through a series of carefully orchestrated steps. The entire process is designed to be repeatable, idempotent, and require zero manual intervention.</p>

    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-50 to-blue-50 dark:from-gray-800 dark:to-gray-700 p-6 rounded-lg border border-primary-200 dark:border-gray-600">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-center">
        <div>
          <div class="text-4xl mb-2">üîß</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Phase 1: Provisioning</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Bare-metal OS installation</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-4xl mb-2">‚öôÔ∏è</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Phase 2: Configuration</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">System hardening and setup</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-4xl mb-2">üöÄ</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Phase 3: Deployment</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Kubernetes cluster creation</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="glass-card p-8 mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">Detailed Workflow Steps</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-primary-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-primary-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400">Step 1: Provisioning Server Setup</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Deploy and configure the provisioning server with all required network services.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Run Ansible playbook to configure DHCP, TFTP, and HTTP services</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Download and prepare Ubuntu installation media</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Generate cloud-init configuration files</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Configure network boot settings and PXE menu</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500">
          Duration: 10-15 minutes
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400">Step 2: Bare-Metal Server Provisioning</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Power on bare-metal servers and let them automatically install Ubuntu via PXE boot.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Server performs PXE network boot</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ DHCP assigns IP and boot configuration</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ TFTP delivers bootloader and kernel</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ HTTP serves installation media and cloud-init configs</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Ubuntu installs automatically with predefined settings</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Server reboots into freshly installed OS</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500">
          Duration: 15-20 minutes per server (parallel execution)
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-green-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-green-700 dark:text-green-400">Step 3: Base System Configuration</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Prepare the freshly installed servers for Kubernetes deployment.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Apply security hardening configurations</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Configure network settings and firewall rules</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Install required system packages and dependencies</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Set up NTP time synchronization</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Configure kernel parameters for Kubernetes</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Disable swap and enable required kernel modules</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500">
          Duration: 5-10 minutes
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-purple-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-400">Step 4: Container Runtime Installation</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Install and configure containerd as the container runtime.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Install containerd and required plugins</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Configure runtime settings and cgroup drivers</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Set up container image registry mirrors</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Enable and start containerd service</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500">
          Duration: 3-5 minutes
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-yellow-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-yellow-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-yellow-700 dark:text-yellow-400">Step 5: Kubernetes Components Installation</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Install kubeadm, kubelet, and kubectl on all nodes.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Add Kubernetes package repositories</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Install specific Kubernetes version</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Configure kubelet service</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Hold packages to prevent automatic updates</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500">
          Duration: 3-5 minutes
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-red-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-red-700 dark:text-red-400">Step 6: Kubernetes Cluster Initialization</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Bootstrap the Kubernetes control plane and join worker nodes.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Initialize first control plane node with kubeadm</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Install pod network plugin (Calico)</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Join additional control plane nodes (HA setup)</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Join worker nodes to the cluster</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Verify cluster health and node status</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500">
          Duration: 10-15 minutes
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-indigo-700 dark:text-indigo-400">Step 7: Storage Layer Deployment</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Deploy Rook Ceph for distributed storage across the cluster.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Deploy Rook operator</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Create Ceph cluster configuration</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Configure storage pools and replication</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Create storage classes for dynamic provisioning</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Verify Ceph cluster health</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500">
          Duration: 15-20 minutes
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-6 py-4 bg-pink-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-r-lg">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-pink-700 dark:text-pink-400">Step 8: Additional Services</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Deploy supporting services and operational tools.</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Install MetalLB for load balancing</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Deploy Ingress controller</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Set up monitoring with Prometheus</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Configure centralized logging</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Install cluster autoscaler (if needed)</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-500">
          Duration: 10-15 minutes
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="glass-card p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Total Deployment Time</h2>
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-50 to-blue-50 dark:from-gray-800 dark:to-gray-700 p-6 rounded-lg border border-primary-200 dark:border-gray-600">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-center mb-6">
        <div>
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 mb-2">60-90 min</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">From bare-metal to production cluster</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400 mb-2">0</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Manual interventions required</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 mb-2">100%</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Repeatable and consistent</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-center text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        The entire workflow is fully automated and can be executed repeatedly to create identical clusters. Infrastructure as Code principles ensure consistency and version control of all configurations.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
